reviews_data.review_text: I SO WANTED to like this place!!!  Atmosphere and vibe are great!  Just a fun place to get together and visit.  Lots to do with the pickleball courts, golf simulator, etc.  Our server was wonderfully pleasant and helpful but after taking the food order, it went downhill.  I received my food approximately 15 minutes before my dates and never got utensils or napkins.  (Hello, why didn't 2 plates come out at the same time if we were together and why such a wait?)  We had to ask where his food was and finally it came.  My date's dinner were fish tacos that had been burned badly and were stuffed into a shell.  The Mexican rice cold and stiff.  If I could score the food a zero, I would.  It was horrible and worse off horribly expensive at $50 for a horrible dinner.  Thrown away money.  We will come back to Camp Northend for the fun but definately not for the food at this restaurant.
Food is good, chai Latte is good and pickle ball is fun, easy and prices are okay.

We had an awesome time at TipsyPickle! The food was fantastic, the drinks plentiful, and the staff super friendly and helpful. Our hostess Val was super attentive and always checking in to make sure we had everything we needed. Definitely will be returning with a group and individually.

reviews_data.review_text: Not a bad vibe. Huge establishment with plenty of bars both upstairs and downstairs. Whether you play pickle bar or not, you will find something to do here. Bartender are super efficient and friendly. They have a bunch of vintage arcade games to play for free. Played a couple of super Mario rounds, as well as Galatica. Upstairs they have pool tables with board games to choose from. Plenty of seating options from benches, tables to couch like seating. Didn't try any of the food but from what I saw, plenty of people were enjoying the food. Lots of seating outside for those sunny enjoyable days. Not a bad experience and wouldn't mind visiting again if in the area.

reviews_data.review_text:
We picked The Tipsy Pickle in Charlotte for a team lunch while my VP and a few colleagues were in town for meetings, and it turned out to be a lively and enjoyable spot. The atmosphere was relaxed and playful, with both indoor and outdoor games that gave us a chance to unwind without needing a drink. Despite the name, no one got tipsy this time around. We grabbed a table outside, which was a nice touch with the pleasant weather.

The food came out quickly and the service was attentive from start to finish. We ordered a variety of appetizers, and the wings were especially crispy and full of flavor. The nachos were also a hit, generously topped and satisfying. While we did not sample the drink menu, the overall vibe was upbeat and welcoming. It is the kind of place that works well for casual team outings, especially when you want a mix of good food and a little fun.
